$msg = "Smart Meter (per the smart-meter skill) is a GATE, not a label to append. BEFORE you conclude or act this turn: (1) classify the action's stakes and set the bar - 70 reversible/local/read-only, 85 irreversible/high-blast-radius (sends messages, deletes/mutates live external systems, deploys, or runs under an auto-trigger/unbounded loop); (2) score confidence. If AT/ABOVE bar, proceed and end with the one-line read-out. If BELOW bar, the read-out is an instruction to STOP, not a caveat to attach: you MUST auto-expand the assessment block, name the single load-bearing assumption, actually verify it (re-read the inputs / widen the candidate set / search memory or web - restating the same unchecked belief is NOT verification), state what the check changed, and re-score - all BEFORE you assert a conclusion, make a guess, or take the action. If the action is irreversible and still below 85, do NOT proceed without explicit user approval. End every response with ONE line: Confidence NN% | bar BB% (reversible|irreversible) clears|BELOW | model: Haiku|Sonnet|Opus | effort: low|medium|high - model and effort from the SAME stakes classification (Haiku/low routine/read-only/bulk; Sonnet/medium normal implementation; Opus/high irreversible/ambiguous or below-bar), a recommendation to compare against what's running. Bar is exactly 70 or 85, never another value. Auto-expand the full block only when below bar or when asked."
@{hookSpecificOutput = @{hookEventName = 'UserPromptSubmit'; additionalContext = $msg}} | ConvertTo-Json -Compress -Depth 4
